title: George Washington Birthplace National Monument: Weather
body: Explore This Park    Plan Your Visit     Things To Know Before You Come     Weather              Weather      The park experiences all four distinct seasons. Temperatures vary in the summer from the 70s to the high 90s with high humidity, typically low 90s with frequent thunder storms. Winters vary from mild and rainy to snow and ice. Temperatures range from the 40s to the teens. Spring and fall are typically pleasant in the 50s and 60s.
